    "fix": {
      "fixes": [
        {
          "id": "premortem-001",
          "status": "fixed",
          "detail": "real_gh_reader now matches the PR by real build-branch prefix (superheroes/<work_item>-<hash>, falling back to legacy wi-<work_item>) instead of the harness's synthetic pr_title, which the live showrunner's gh pr create --fill-first never sets as the PR title."
        },
        {
          "id": "code-reviewer-artifact-discovery-glob",
          "status": "fixed",
          "detail": "real_discover_artifacts now globs both the legacy wi-<stamp>* pattern and the real showrunner superheroes/*<stamp>* pattern, and discovers PRs by headRefName instead of a free-text title search; the discovered PR artifact's name is now its head branch so acceptance_cleanup.plan's parse_stamp routing still finds the stamp. real_reap's PR branch now looks the PR back up by --head instead of --search."
        },
        {
          "id": "code-reviewer-reclaim-dead-cleanup-gap",
          "status": "fixed",
          "detail": "invoke() now calls a new _discovery_teardown(deps) (record-less discovery mode, run_stamp=None) on a confirmed-dead reclaim, before this invocation's own materialize/launch, and folds its cleaned_up/left_behind into the orphan record instead of hardcoding empty lists."
        },
        {
          "id": "code-001-headless-flag",
          "status": "already-fixed-in-worktree",
          "detail": "Prior commits in this worktree (52c333a, 9ed7e02) already replaced claude --headless with claude -p <prompt> driving superheroes:showrunner, fixed the real_run_outcome field-name mismatch, exported LIB in the SKILL.md front door, and fixed the spend_partial effort-key bug."
        }
      ],
      "deferred": [
        {
          "id": "architecture-phase-vocabulary-mismatch",
          "reason": "PIPELINE_PHASES (harness) vs showrunner.js's real PHASES vocabulary and terminal-state shape are structurally decoupled -- runPhases never accumulates a traversed-phases list into its {outcome,phase,reason} terminal return. Fixing this requires a core showrunner.js loop change (accumulating phase history across runPhases and threading it through every terminal return site: front-half-boundary park, reconcile park, startup park, phase-progress-failure park, and shipPhase's ready/parked returns) w"
        },
        {
          "id": "code-002-fr9-retry-dead-path",
          "reason": "Original reviewer flagged this Low-confidence with an explicit tradeoff note: whether the failure-kind-to-environmental mapping was a deliberate live-run/DoD deferral is a judgment call, not a clear-cut bug. No real production signal in the launcher/child-factory path cleanly maps to the ENVIRONMENTAL kinds (check-runner-errored-before-running, host-unreachable) without inventing new showrunner-side semantics, so a speculative fix risked being wrong rather than useful."
        }
      ],
      "changedSubjectDetails": [
        "Code",
